The numbers are placed on the grid in an anticlockwise squareâ€‘spiral:

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
5&4&3\\[2pt]
6&1&2\\[2pt]
7&8&9
\end{array}
\]

For a number \(n\) let \((x,y)\) be its coordinates (with the centre \(1\) at \((0,0)\) and \(x\) increasing to the right, \(y\) increasing upward).

---

### 1.  Coordinates of a given number  

If \(k=\max(|x|,|y|)\) then the outer layer \(k\) ends with the odd square  

\[
M_k=(2k+1)^2
\]

which lies at \((k,-k)\).  
For any point \((x,y)\) on the same layer we have  

\[
n=M_k-d,\qquad
\begin{cases}
\text{bottom side } (y=-k): & d=k-x, \\
\text{left side   } (x=-k): & d=2k+(y+k),\\
\text{top side    } (y= k): & d=4k+(x+k),\\
\text{right side  } (x= k): & d=6k+(k-y).
\end{cases}
\]

---

### 2.  Locate \(2026\)

\(2026\) lies between \(45^2=2025\) and \(47^2=2209\); hence it is on layer  

\[
k=23,\qquad M_{23}=47^2=2209 .
\]

\(d = M_{23}-2026 = 183\).

Since \(6k=138\) and \(d>138\), the point is on the **right side**:

\[
y = k-(d-6k)=23-(183-138)= -22 .
\]

Thus  

\[
2026\; \longleftrightarrow\; (x,y)=(23,-22).
\]

---

### 3.  The eight neighbours  

The neighbour coordinates are  

\[
\begin{aligned}
&(24,-21),\;(24,-22),\;(24,-23),\\
&(23,-21),\;(23,-23),\\
&(22,-21),\;(22,-22),\;(22,-23).
\end{aligned}
\]

Applying the formulas above gives the corresponding numbers:

| \((x,y)\) | \(k\) | side | \(d\) | neighbour |
|-----------|------|------|------|-----------|
| (24,-21) | 24 | right | \(6\cdot24+(24-(-21))=189\) | \(2401-189=2212\) |
| (24,-22) | 24 | right | 190 | \(2211\) |
| (24,-23) | 24 | right | 191 | \(2210\) |
| (23,-21) | 23 | right | \(6\cdot23+(23-(-21))=182\) | \(2027\) |
| (23,-23) | 23 | bottom| \(23-23=0\) | \(2209\) |
| (22,-21) | 22 | right | \(6\cdot22+(22-(-21))=175\) | \(1850\) |
| (22,-22) | 22 | bottom| \(22-22=0\) | \(2025\) |
| (22,-23) | 23 | bottom| \(23-22=1\) | \(2208\) |

So the eight neighbours are  

\[
2212,\;2211,\;2210,\;2027,\;2209,\;1850,\;2025,\;2208 .
\]

---

### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum} &=2212+2211+2210+2027+2209+1850+2025+2208\\
&=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
